OL,4,CCovid in Scotland: Confusion over
OL,5,C'vertical drinking' rules in pubs
OL,6, The Scottish government has been urged
OL,7, to clarify whether "vertical drinking"
OL,8, will be allowed in pubs from next week.
OL,10,FDrinking while standing at bar has not
OL,11,Fbeen permitted since lockdown easing in
OL,12,Fa bid to limit the spread of Covid.
OL,14,FDeputy First Minister John Swinney told
OL,15,FBBC Radio's Good Morning Scotland that
OL,16,Fwould remain the case when most
OL,17,Frestrictions are lifted on 9 August.
OL,19,FBut a senior figure in the Scottish
OL,20,FBeer & Pub Association later tweeted it
OL,21,Fhas been given the green light.
